                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12622.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 25, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Secretary of Foreign Relations Fabela has acknowledged receipt of a note handed
                    General Carranza by Silliman July 19 containing the points set forth in
                    Department’s July 16, 7 p.m. Fabela says: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Referring to your unofficial note in which you embody the telegram from
                            Secretary Bryan, also to the verbal expression made by Mr. Carranza to
                            you, to Mr. Silliman and Mr. Robertson in their conference of the 19th,
                            the First Chief instructs me to thank Mr. Bryan for the expressions
                            which he conveyed through you to Mr. Carranza. Both Mr. Carranza and I
                            desire to express to you, Mr. Consul General, and to Mr. Silliman and
                            Mr. Robertson our appreciation of your desire that our strife may soon
                            end in a satisfactory manner.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
